GetPremiumLimit.description: Returns information about a limit, increased for Premium users. Returns a 404 error if the limit is unknown

GetPremiumFeatures.description: Returns information about features, available to Premium users

source.description: Source of the request; pass null if the method is called from some non-standard source

GetPremiumStickerExamples.description: Returns examples of premium stickers for demonstration purposes

ViewPremiumFeature.description: Informs TDLib that the user viewed detailed information about a Premium feature on the Premium features screen

ClickPremiumSubscriptionButton.description: Informs TDLib that the user clicked Premium subscription button on the Premium features screen

GetPremiumState.description: Returns state of Telegram Premium subscription and promotion videos for Premium features

CanPurchasePremium.description: Checks whether Telegram Premium purchase is possible. Must be called before in-store Premium purchase

AssignAppStoreTransaction.description: Informs server about a purchase through App Store. For official applications only

AssignGooglePlayTransaction.description: Informs server about a purchase through Google Play. For official applications only

store_product_id.description: Identifier of the purchased store product

SearchStringsByPrefix.description: Searches specified query by word prefixes in the provided strings. Returns 0-based positions of strings that matched. Can be called synchronously

strings.description: The strings to search in for the query

limit.description: The maximum number of objects to return

return_none_for_empty_query.description: Pass true to receive no results for an empty query

SendCustomRequest.description: Sends a custom request; for bots only

AnswerCustomQuery.description: Answers a custom query; for bots only

SetAlarm.description: Succeeds after a specified amount of time has passed. Can be called before initialization

seconds.description: Number of seconds before the function returns

GetCountries.description: Returns information about existing countries. Can be called before authorization

GetCountryCode.description: Uses the current IP address to find the current country. Returns two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code. Can be called before authorization

GetPhoneNumberInfo.description: Returns information about a phone number by its prefix. Can be called before authorization

GetPhoneNumberInfoSync.description: Returns information about a phone number by its prefix synchronously. getCountries must be called at least once after changing localization to the specified language if properly localized country information is expected. Can be called synchronously

language_code.description: A two-letter ISO 639-1 language code for country information localization

GetDeepLinkInfo.description: Returns information about a tg:// deep link. Use "tg://need_update_for_some_feature" or "tg:some_unsupported_feature" for testing. Returns a 404 error for unknown links. Can be called before authorization

GetApplicationConfig.description: Returns application config, provided by the server. Can be called before authorization

AddApplicationChangelog.description: Adds server-provided application changelog as messages to the chat 777000 (Telegram) or as a stories; for official applications only. Returns a 404 error if nothing changed

SaveApplicationLogEvent.description: Saves application log event on the server. Can be called before authorization

chat_id.description: Optional chat identifier, associated with the event

GetApplicationDownloadLink.description: Returns the link for downloading official Telegram application to be used when the current user invites friends to Telegram

AddProxy.description: Adds a proxy server for network requests. Can be called before authorization

server.description: Proxy server domain or IP address

enable.description: Pass true to immediately enable the proxy

EditProxy.description: Edits an existing proxy server for network requests. Can be called before authorization

server.description: Proxy server domain or IP address

enable.description: Pass true to immediately enable the proxy

EnableProxy.description: Enables a proxy. Only one proxy can be enabled at a time. Can be called before authorization

DisableProxy.description: Disables the currently enabled proxy. Can be called before authorization

RemoveProxy.description: Removes a proxy server. Can be called before authorization

GetProxies.description: Returns list of proxies that are currently set up. Can be called before authorization

GetProxyLink.description: Returns an HTTPS link, which can be used to add a proxy. Available only for SOCKS5 and MTProto proxies. Can be called before authorization

PingProxy.description: Computes time needed to receive a response from a Telegram server through a proxy. Can be called before authorization

proxy_id.description: Proxy identifier. Use 0 to ping a Telegram server without a proxy

SetLogStream.description: Sets new log stream for internal logging of TDLib. Can be called synchronously

GetLogStream.description: Returns information about currently used log stream for internal logging of TDLib. Can be called synchronously

SetLogVerbosityLevel.description: Sets the verbosity level of the internal logging of TDLib. Can be called synchronously

new_verbosity_level.description: New value of the verbosity level for logging. Value 0 corresponds to fatal errors, value 1 corresponds to errors, value 2 corresponds to warnings and debug warnings,

GetLogVerbosityLevel.description: Returns current verbosity level of the internal logging of TDLib. Can be called synchronously

GetLogTags.description: Returns list of available TDLib internal log tags, for example, ["actor", "binlog", "connections", "notifications", "proxy"]. Can be called synchronously

SetLogTagVerbosityLevel.description: Sets the verbosity level for a specified TDLib internal log tag. Can be called synchronously

tag.description: Logging tag to change verbosity level

GetLogTagVerbosityLevel.description: Returns current verbosity level for a specified TDLib internal log tag. Can be called synchronously

tag.description: Logging tag to change verbosity level

AddLogMessage.description: Adds a message to TDLib internal log. Can be called synchronously

verbosity_level.description: The minimum verbosity level needed for the message to be logged; 0-1023

text.description: Text of a message to log

GetUserSupportInfo.description: Returns support information for the given user; for Telegram support only

SetUserSupportInfo.description: Sets support information for the given user; for Telegram support only

GetSupportName.description: Returns localized name of the Telegram support user; for Telegram support only

TestCallEmpty.description: Does nothing; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

TestCallString.description: Returns the received string; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

TestCallBytes.description: Returns the received bytes; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

TestCallVectorInt.description: Returns the received vector of numbers; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

TestCallVectorIntObject.description: Returns the received vector of objects containing a number; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

TestCallVectorString.description: Returns the received vector of strings; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

TestCallVectorStringObject.description: Returns the received vector of objects containing a string; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

TestSquareInt.description: Returns the squared received number; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

TestNetwork.description: Sends a simple network request to the Telegram servers; for testing only. Can be called before authorization

TestProxy.description: Sends a simple network request to the Telegram servers via proxy; for testing only. Can be called before authorization

server.description: Proxy server domain or IP address

dc_id.description: Identifier of a datacenter with which to test connection

timeout.description: The maximum overall timeout for the request

TestGetDifference.description: Forces an updates.getDifference call to the Telegram servers; for testing only

TestUseUpdate.description: Does nothing and ensures that the Update object is used; for testing only. This is an offline method. Can be called before authorization

TestReturnError.description: Returns the specified error and ensures that the Error object is used; for testing only. Can be called synchronously
